---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';
import AuthorInfo from '../../components/AuthorInfo.astro';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Highest Scoring 2-Letter Words in Scrabble — Complete Ranking"
  description="Complete ranking of ALL 2-letter Scrabble words by score. QI and ZA top at 11pts, XI and XU at 9pts, KY at 9pts (SOWPODS). Use our free word finder tool."
  keywords="highest scoring 2 letter words scrabble, qi scrabble points, za scrabble, xi scrabble word, two letter words ranked, best 2 letter scrabble words, 2 letter word scores"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Highest Scoring 2-Letter Words in Scrabble — Complete Ranking",
    "description": "Complete ranking of ALL 2-letter Scrabble words by score. QI and ZA top at 11pts, XI and XU at 9pts. Full table with strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "dateModified": "2026-06-08",
    "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Raj Naik", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/about/" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/highest-scoring-2-letter-words" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the highest scoring 2-letter word in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QI and ZA are tied at 11 points each. QI (Q=10, I=1) is the life force in Chinese philosophy. ZA (Z=10, A=1) is slang for pizza. Both are valid in TWL and SOWPODS and are essential for dumping Q and Z tiles." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is KY a valid 2-letter Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KY is valid in SOWPODS (international dictionary) only, scoring 9 points (K=5, Y=4). It is NOT valid in TWL (North American tournament play). KY means cows in Scottish dialect. If playing internationally, it ties with XI and XU as the second-highest 2-letter word." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many 2-letter words are there in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "TWL (North American) has 107 valid 2-letter words. SOWPODS (international) has 127. The extra 20 SOWPODS words include CH, FY, GU, IO, JA, KY, NY, OB, OU, ST, TE, UG, and others. Memorizing all valid 2-letter words is considered the single biggest skill improvement for new players." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-4 pb-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Highest Scoring 2 Letter Words" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Highest Scoring 2-Letter Words in Scrabble — Complete Ranking</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Two-letter words are the backbone of competitive Scrabble. They let you play parallel, hook existing words, and dump high-value tiles in tight spots. Here's the complete ranking from highest to lowest score.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QI / ZA (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">107</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">127</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOWPODS Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XI / XU (#2)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 5 Highest Scoring 2-Letter Words</h2>
      <p>These are the two-letter words that score the most points. QI and ZA dominate because Q and Z are worth 10 points each.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 #1 Tied</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QI & ZA — 11 Points Each</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">QI: Q=10, I=1 · ZA: Z=10, A=1 · Both valid TWL + SOWPODS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">QI is the Chinese concept of life force. ZA is informal for pizza. These two words save games — they let you dump Q without U and Z without building a long word. On a Triple Letter Score, QI hits 31 points.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">#2 · XI & XU</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts each · X=8 + vowel · Both TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">#3 · KY (SOWPODS only)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · K=5, Y=4 · Scottish for cows · Not in TWL</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">#4 · MY & BY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts each · M/B=3 + Y=4 · Common and versatile</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">#5 · CH (SOWPODS only)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · C=3, H=4 · Letter name · Not in TWL</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete Score Tiers</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">11pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">QI, ZA</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">9pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">XI, XU, KY*</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">7pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">MY, BY, CH*</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">6pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">AX, EX, OX, HM, SH</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">5pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">AH, EH, OH, UH, AW, OW, WE, WO, JO, KA, FE, HI, HO, HA, HE</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">2-4pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">80+ common words</span></span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 text-center">* SOWPODS only — not valid in TWL (North American tournaments)</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for High-Scoring 2-Letter Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QI on Triple Letter Score:</span> Place Q on a TLS and QI scores 31 points (10×3 + 1). This is often the best play for Q — no need to find a QU word when QI alone scores higher than most 5-letter words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays with XI/XU:</span> Play XI or XU parallel to an existing word. Each letter that touches a tile above/below scores separately — a well-placed parallel can net 20+ points from a 2-letter play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZA for Z flexibility:</span> ZA plays anywhere you have an open A. It's the fastest way to dump Z without needing a longer word. On a DLS, ZA scores 21 points from just two tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Know your dictionary:</span> If playing SOWPODS, KY and CH give you two extra 7+ point options. If playing TWL, focus on QI, ZA, XI, XU as your power plays. Knowing which dictionary you're using changes your 2-letter strategy completely.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Pro Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Memorizing all <span class="text-white font-medium">107 two-letter words</span> (TWL) is considered the single biggest improvement a player can make. It opens up parallel plays, hook extensions, and board positions that are invisible to players who only know common words.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-qi-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is QI a Scrabble Word? — Yes, and Here's Why It Matters</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-za-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZA a Scrabble Word? — Valid in Both Dictionaries</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-my-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is MY a Scrabble Word? — 7 Points From Two Tiles</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔍 Check any 2-letter word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why This Matters for Your Game</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Building a strong vocabulary is the single biggest predictor of Scrabble success. Players who know <span class="text-white font-medium">more valid words score 30-50% higher</span> on average than those relying on common vocabulary alone.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">30%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Score improvement</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 min</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Daily study needed</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Free</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No signup required</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Whether you are preparing for tournament play or just want to beat your family at game night, the words on this page give you a competitive edge that compounds over time.</p>


<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Quick Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Practice with the solver:</span> Enter your rack tiles into our free word finder to discover every valid combination. Seeing all options trains your pattern recognition over time.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorise in groups:</span> Rather than learning words randomly, study them by pattern — same prefix, same suffix, or same tile combination. Grouped learning is 3x more effective than isolated word lists.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Test yourself daily:</span> Pick 5 words from this page each day and try to use them in practice games. Active recall beats passive reading for long-term retention.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Explore More</p>
  <div class="grid gap-2">
    <a href="/blog/how-to-improve-at-scrabble-fast/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
      <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">How to Improve at Scrabble Fast</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-bag-distribution/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
      <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Scrabble Tile Bag Distribution — All 100 Tiles</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Memory Technique</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Group these words into <span class="text-white font-medium">clusters of 5</span> and learn one cluster per day. After a week, test yourself on all 35 — you will retain 80%+ using spaced repetition. Review any forgotten words the following day.</p>
</div>

<p>The most effective Scrabble study habit is short, daily sessions rather than long weekly marathons. Five minutes of focused word review every day builds permanent memory faster than an hour once a week.</p>


<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Scoring Patterns</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">High-Value Tiles</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10), Z(10), X(8), J(8) — power tiles that transform ordinary words into premium scorers when placed on letter multipliers.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Mid-Value Tiles</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">K(5), H(4), W(4), V(4), F(4), Y(4) — often overlooked but consistently add 4-5 points per word. Pair with common tiles for reliable scoring.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Bingo Bonus (+50)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Use all 7 tiles for the bingo bonus. Words 7+ letters long from this page are potential bingo candidates worth memorising specifically.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Parallel Plays</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Short words placed alongside existing words create multiple crossings. Each crossing scores independently — a 3-letter parallel can yield 20+ points.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    
      <AuthorInfo updated="June 8, 2026" />

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
